Evaluate the horizontal asymptotes, if any, of the function {eq}y = x^2 + \dfrac{1}{x^2 - 1}

{/eq} using limits. Given:

{eq}f(x) = x^2 + \dfrac{1}{x^2 - 1}\\[2ex]

{/eq}

First, find the decimals of the function at both positive and negative infinity.

{eq}\begin{align*}

\lim_{x\to\infty} x^2 + \dfrac{1}{x^2 - 1}&=\infty + \dfrac{1}{\infty - 1}\\[2ex]

&=\infty + 0\\[2ex]

&=\infty\\[2ex]

\end{align*}

{/eq}

{eq}\begin{align*}

\lim_{x\to-\infty} x^2 + \dfrac{1}{x^2 - 1}&=\infty + \dfrac{1}{\infty - 1}\\[2ex]

&=\infty + 0\\[2ex]

&=\infty\\[2ex]

\end{align*}

{/eq}

Since the limits at both positive and negative infinity are infinity, there is no horizontal asymptote.

Differentiate the function \( \cosh(2 - 5x^5) + \arcsin(x + 2) \). \[
\begin{align*}
\frac{d}{dx}[\cosh(2 - 5x^5) + \arcsin(x + 2)] &= \frac{d}{dx}[\cosh(2 - 5x^5)] + \frac{d}{dx}[\arcsin(x + 2)] \\
&= \sinh(2 - 5x^5) \cdot \frac{d}{dx}(2 - 5x^5) + \frac{1}{\sqrt{1 - (x + 2)^2}} \cdot \frac{d}{dx}(x + 2) \\
&= \sinh(2 - 5x^5) \cdot (-5 \cdot 5x^4) + \frac{1}{\sqrt{1 - (x + 2)^2}} \cdot 1 \\
&= -20x^4 \sinh(2 - 5x^5) + \frac{1}{\sqrt{1 - (x + 2)^2}}.
\end{align*}
\]

